2 HOUSE BILL 575
1 Section 7–301.4
2 Annotated Code of Maryland
3 (2025 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
4 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
5 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
6 Article – Education
7 7–301.4.
8 (A) IN THIS SECTION, “PUBLIC FACING LEGISLATIVE BODY” MEANS AN
9 ENTITY THAT:
10 (1) MEETS TO SET OR CARRY OUT PUBLIC POLICY;
11 (2) IS SUBJECT TO THE OPEN MEETINGS ACT; AND
12 (3) CONSISTS OF MEMBERS WHO ARE ELECTED OR APPOINTED BY
13 THE GOVERNOR OR A LOCAL EXECUTIVE AUTHORITY.
14 (B) (1) SUBJECT TO SUBSECTION (B) (C) OF THIS SECTION, THE
15 DEPARTMENT AND EACH COUNTY BOARD SHALL ADOPT AN ATTENDANCE POLICY
16 FOR PUBLIC SCHOOL STUDENTS THAT TREATS A STUDENT’S ABSENCE AS EXCUSED
17 IF, DURING A REGULAR SESSION OF THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY A PUBLIC FACING
18 BODY, THE STUDENT:
19 (B) (1) THE STUDENT ATTENDANCE POLICY OF A COUNTY BOARD SHALL
20 INCLUDE A PROVISION ALLOWING AN EXCUSED OR DISCRETIONARY ABSENCE FOR A
21 PUBLIC SCHOOL STUDENT PARTICIPATING IN CIVIC ENGAGEMENT ACTIVITIES.
22 (2) CIVIC ENGAGEMENT ACTIVITIES SHALL INCLUDE:
23 (I) TESTIFIES TESTIFYING VIRTUALLY OR IN PERSON AT A
24 HEARING OF ANY COMMITTEE OF THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY A PUBLIC FACING
25 LEGISLATIVE BODY; OR
26 (II) CONDUCTS CIVIC ENGAGEMENT ACTIVITIES, INCLUDING:
27 1. MEETING WITH LEGISLATORS MEMBERS OF THE A
28 PUBLIC FACING LEGISLATIVE BODY; AND

HOUSE BILL 575 3
1 2. (III) ADVOCATING FOR OR AGAINST LEGISLATION
2 AND CONTRIBUTING TO THE CONSIDERATION, DEVELOPMENT, OR
3 IMPLEMENTATION OF POLICY ISSUES; AND
4 3. OTHER ACTIVITIES DEEMED TO BE CIVIC
5 ENGAGEMENT BY THE DEPARTMENT AND THE APPLICABLE COUNTY BOARD OR AND
6 (III) (IV) PARTICIPATES PARTICIPATING IN THE MARYLAND
7 GENERAL ASSEMBLY PAGE PROGRAM.
8 (2) (3) (I) IF THE ATTENDANCE POLICY REQUIRES A NOTE TO
9 EXCUSE AN ABSENCE, THE POLICY SHALL AUTHORIZE AN APPROPRIATE
10 REPRESENTATIVE TO PROVIDE A NOTE OR REASONABLE DOCUMENTATION TO
11 EXCUSE THE STUDENT’S ABSENCE.
12 (II) AN EXCUSED ABSENCE UNDER THIS SECTION IS A LAWFUL
13 ABSENCE AND MAY NOT BE INCLUDED IN A CALCULATION OF CHRONIC
14 ABSENTEEISM FOR THE STUDENT OR THE SCHOOL.
15 (B) (C) (1) A COUNTY BOARD SHALL ADOPT POLICIES AND
16 PROCEDURES TO CARRY OUT THE REQUIREMENTS OF THIS SECTION.
17 (2) POLICIES AND PROCEDURES ADOPTED UNDER THIS SUBSECTION
18 SHALL AUTHORIZE A STUDENT TO BE EXCUSED FOR AT:
19 (I) AT LEAST 15 HOURS OR 2 SCHOOL DAYS TO TESTIFY OR
20 CONDUCT CIVIC ENGAGEMENT ACTIVITIES UNDER SUBSECTION (A)(1) (B)(1)(I) OR
21 (II) OF THIS SECTION; OR
22 (II) THE LENGTH OF TIME OF THE PAGE PROGRAM FOR CIVIC
23 ENGAGEMENT CONDUCTED UNDER SUBSECTION (B)(1)(III) OF THIS SECTION.
24 (3) EXCUSED ABSENCES FOR TESTIFYING OR CONDUCTING CIVIC
25 ENGAGEMENT ACTIVITIES UNDER SUBSECTION (B)(1) OF THIS SECTION SHALL BE IN
26 ADDITION TO ANY EXCUSED ABSENCES UNDER EXISTING POLICIES OR PROCEDURES
27 OF THE COUNTY BOARD.
28 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
29 1, 2026.

